The company develops its own technology with in-house developers to satisfy the needs of the Spanish speaking population that has no website in its own language. Established for two years, Summitour has developed Spanish and English language versions of its site, which are currently up and running, providing more than 110,000 hotels, 17,000 rental car sites, 3,000 activities, 800 airline destinations, and more than 800 escorted tours in Europe, Asia, Africa, Southwest Pacific and Middle East. The Company is in the process of patenting and developing Paytours. Paytours Convenient is an installment payment system for customers who don't have the funds up front for a vacation but wish to purchase a trip on layaway. Paytours Gift will enable friends or family to establish a group fund for newlyweds, high school or college graduates, ""quinceañeras"", or anyone achieving a significant milestone.  The Hispanic market exceeds 50 million and continues to grow rapidly, with a buying power that exceeds $1 trillion. Summitour's mission is to design and offer a wide range of high-quality tourism products to satisfy the tastes, needs, and requirements of the Spanish-speaking travelers in the U.S. and Latin America.

Full Description: Medicarease is a leading healthcare solutions provider dedicated to simplifying the complex world of Medicare for individuals, families, and healthcare providers. We understand that navigating the Medicare system can be overwhelming, and our mission is to make the process seamless and stress-free for everyone involved. Our Mission: At Medicarease, our mission is to empower individuals with knowledge and support to make informed decisions about their Medicare options. We aim to demystify the intricacies of Medicare, ensuring that beneficiaries receive the coverage they need while maximizing their benefits and minimizing costs. Services: Medicare Education and Guidance: We offer comprehensive educational resources to help beneficiaries understand the different parts of Medicare, including Part A, Part B, Part C (Medicare Advantage), Part D (Prescription Drug Coverage), and Medigap (Supplemental Insurance). Our team of experts assists individuals in choosing the most suitable plan based on their unique healthcare needs and budget. Enrollment Assistance: Medicarease provides personalized assistance throughout the enrollment process. Our knowledgeable advisors guide beneficiaries through the application process, ensuring all necessary paperwork is completed accurately and on time. Medicare Advantage and Prescription Drug Plans (Part C and Part D): We help individuals explore a wide range of Medicare Advantage and Prescription Drug Plans available in their area. By analyzing various plans and their specific benefits, we aim to match beneficiaries with options that best suit their healthcare requirements and financial preferences. Medigap (Supplemental Insurance) Plans: Understanding that Original Medicare may leave some coverage gaps, we offer guidance on Medigap plans to provide additional benefits, such as copayment and coinsurance coverage, that can help reduce out-of-pocket expenses. Medicare Seminars and Workshops: Medicarease conducts educational seminars and workshops in collaboration with community organizations and senior centers. These events offer valuable insights into Medicare, address common concerns, and provide attendees with opportunities to ask questions. Why Choose Medicarease: Expertise and Experience: Our team consists of highly trained professionals with extensive knowledge of the Medicare system. We stay updated with the latest changes and developments in the healthcare industry to offer the best advice to our clients. Personalized Approach: At Medicarease, we believe in personalized service. We take the time to understand each individual's unique healthcare needs, financial situation, and preferences to recommend the most suitable Medicare plan. Unbiased Recommendations: As an independent company, we are not affiliated with any insurance providers. This independence ensures that our recommendations are entirely unbiased, focusing solely on the best interests of our clients. Exceptional Customer Support: We prioritize excellent customer service and are committed to being responsive, approachable, and supportive throughout our clients' Medicare journey. Conclusion: Medicarease is your trusted partner in navigating the complexities of Medicare. With our expertise, dedication, and commitment to personalized service, we strive to empower beneficiaries to make well-informed decisions about their healthcare coverage. Whether you are new to Medicare or seeking to explore better options, Medicarease is here to make your Medicare experience easy and hassle-free.

The purpose of the Board is to direct the planning and financial management of the Foundation, and to direct all of the philanthropic activities to support our hospice.  The Mountain Valley Hospice Foundation was formed in 2013 to encourage gifts in support of our mission from a generous community and supportive local businesses and foundations.  The Board members are deeply committed to and passionate about the mission of the Foundation and dedicate countless hours to advocate and raise critical funding for Hospice.  There are many ways that you can make a gift to Mountain Valley Hospice and some of the most common are listed below along with their tax benefits. Please consult your own professional advisor before considering any type of planned gift.  A Charitable Gift Annuity is a simple contract between a donor and Hospice in which Hospice agrees to pay the donor an income for the rest of his or her life in exchange for a minimum donation.  In a charitable gift annuity, the donation, or principal, is an irrevocable gift which becomes the property of Mountain Valley Hospice upon the death of the donor.

Thermaquatica is commercializing a proprietary and patented technology for processing biomass (including agricultural wastes).
Full Description: Thermaquatica is commercializing a proprietary and patented technology for processing biomass (including agricultural wastes), coal, oil sands, and oil shales to high value platform chemicals and liquid fuels. The method, known as Oxidative Hydrothermal Dissolution (OHD) is simple, using only hot (subcritical) liquid water and oxygen to break down these macromolecular organic materials into their constituent aromatic and aliphatic compounds. The OHD process can also be used for environmental remediation of organic-containing sites, such as oil sands tailings and coal waste ponds. This modular, environmentally–friendly process produces very little CO2, giving the technology a low carbon footprint. OHD requires no pre-treatment of the feed, or additional catalysts, enzymes or solvents (other than water). The OHD bioliquor can be used as a fulvate-type biostimulant and soil enhancer, and high-value, platform biochemicals can also be recovered as saleable products through an add-on option to the main conversion process. The product suite depends on the choice of feedstock and the process conditions. Thermaquatica’s goal is to use OHD technology to produce chemicals similar or identical to petroleum-derived products, using low-cost alternative raw materials such as waste biomass or coal. The resulting products can be sold as fine chemicals, used in manufacturing of biodegradable plastics and polymers, and/or converted to liquid fuels. The OHD technology is described in more detail on the Technology tab from the menu above, and the process is also described in a short video clip in the Media section.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Biotechnology, Natural Resources, Real Estate, Science and Engineering

Description: Dr. Kenneth Hughes (Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes) is a Harvard-educated, Harvard-trained, board-certified plastic surgeon in Los Angeles
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Dr. Kenneth Hughes is a Harvard-educated, board-certified plastic surgeon in Los Angeles. Dr. Kenneth Hughes achieved the highest level of education and elite training prior to practicing in Los Angeles and Beverly Hills. Dr. Kenneth Hughes received his honors degree from Harvard University in 1999. He graduated from medical school in the top 5% of his class and scored in the top 1% nationally on his licensing boards. He was awarded entrance into one of the very selective integrated plastic surgery programs, in which he received extensive training for six years in the vast array of general and plastic surgery procedures. From residency, Dr. Kenneth Hughes was selected as only the second plastic surgeon to pursue a year long aesthetic and cosmetic surgery fellowship at Harvard Medical School. Dr. Hughes has authored numerous papers and textbook chapters on cosmetic surgery topics including face and neck lifts, rhinoplasty and nose surgery, breast augmentation, fat grafting, fillers, scars and scar revision, the preoperative workup for plastic surgery, and photography in plastic surgery. Dr. Kenneth Hughes specializes in performing virtually scarless or minimal scar surgery for the face, nose, and breast. Some of these techniques include short scar face lift, facial fat grafting (facelift technique without visible scars), closed rhinoplasty (no visible external scars), chin implants with no external scar, short scar tummy tuck, and TUBA (breast augmentation without scars on your breasts). In addition, Dr. Kenneth Hughes performs the entire array of plastic and cosmetic surgery procedures. He performs breast augmentation through any incision possible, breast lift, breast reduction, brow lift, upper and lower eyelid surgery, liposuction, liposuction revision, tummy tuck, Brazilian buttlift or BBL, butt implant, silicone and hydrogel removal, removal of fat necrosis (fat death or dead fat), mommy makeover, body lift, arm lift, thigh lift, labiaplasty, and vaginoplasty.  Dr. Kenneth Hughes has a great deal of experience in performing multiple procedure cases (tummy tuck, breast augmentation) or (facelift, upper and lower eyelids) or (breast augmentation, liposculpture).  If you want to have multiple procedures performed, Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes, MD is the plastic surgeon for you.  Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes performs multiple procedure surgeries every day, sometimes several times a day.  How does this benefit YOU, the patient? This means Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes can perform multiple procedures efficiently, effectively, and safely. While some plastic surgeons may take 5 or 6 hours to perform a tummy tuck and breast augmentation, Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes routinely performs these surgeries in under 2 hours. This means that Dr. Kenneth Hughes saves you 3 hours of general anesthesia. The risks of prolonged general anesthesia are manifold. The extra time can put you at increased risk of blood clots, which can travel to the lungs and cause respiratory compromise and even death. The risk of infection and hypothermia as well coagulopathy (bleeding) increases. The list goes on and on. In addition, Dr. Kenneth Hughesis a consultant and lecturer for the Institute for Safety in Office-Based Surgery (ISOBS), a nonprofit patient safety advocacy organization started by Harvard professors. Don’t forget that in addition to preserving your health, Dr. Hughes’s faster operating times translate into saving you money on anesthesia and operating room costs. However, Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes never compromises on quality and the result of your plastic surgery as evidenced by his Before and After Photo Galleries. Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes specializes in performing virtually scarless or minimal scar surgery for the face, nose, and breast, and he offers the most advanced technologies available including fat grafting with stem cell rejuvenation.  Some of these techniques include short scar face lift, facial fat grafting (facelift technique without visible scars), closed rhinoplasty (no visible external scars), chin implants with no external scar, short scar tummy tuck, and TUBA (breast augmentation without scars on your breasts). In addition, Dr. Kenneth Benjamin Hughes performs the entire array of plastic and cosmetic surgery procedures.  He performs breast augmentations through any incision possible, breast lifts, breast reductions, rhinoplasties, facial fat grafting, brow lifts, face lifts, upper and lower eyelid surgeries, chin implants, liposuction/liposculpture, tummy tucks, butt lifts and butt augmentations, mommy makeovers, arm lifts, thigh lifts, labial rejuvenation, and so much more.
